metatags.og:title: Reporting Requirements for Data Breaches
metatags.og:description:
Montana statutes governing data breaches require businesses to notify affected Montana residents if the resident’s personal information is compromised. The notice must be made without reasonable delay, consistent with the legitimate needs of law enforcement.

metatags.og:title: Reported Data Breaches
metatags.og:description:
Data breaches are damaging, costly, and put the personal information of Montana residents at risk.
These breaches can occur due to intentional hacking, criminal cyber-attacks, or human error.  Montana statutes governing data breaches require businesses to notify affected consumers if the consumer’s personal information is compromised.
